cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the problem of vehicle re-identification using deep neural networks and spatio-temporal information. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a two-stage framework that incorporates complex spatio-temporal information, which involves the use of machine learning techniques such as MRF and LSTM. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with video surveillance, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also discusses the challenges of vehicle re-identification, which could be relevant to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
